<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/803.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                        Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In regard to your telegram March 16, promptly take steps necessary to
                                safeguard all legitimate American interests, consulting colleagues
                                where jointly concerned. The Russian Government has signified
                                readiness in principle to participate in present advances and to
                                designate Russo-Asiatic Bank as agent. Can not competing Russian
                                interests be satisfied on basis of assured participation in pending
                                loans?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>